:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:466:\"<p>Looking for the best social media plugins for WordPress? Social media is an extremely powerful tool that can help boost your SEO strategy. This is because it&#8217;s a great platform for driving traffic to your website. It&#8217;s also great at&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-social-media-plugins-for-wordpress-compared/\">The 7 Best Social Media Plugins for WordPress (Compared)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28332:\"<p>Looking for the best social media plugins for WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Social media is an extremely powerful tool that can help <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"boost your SEO strategy\">boost your SEO strategy</a>. This is because it&#8217;s a great platform for driving traffic to your website. It&#8217;s also great at encouraging visitors to engage with your content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason you should invest in your social media strategy is that social proof is becoming increasingly important for businesses and content creators.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All these benefits of social media have a direct impact on the revenue your website generates.  Therefore, having a solid social media game is essential.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why you must install the best social media plugin on your WordPress site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Choose a Social Media Plugin for WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A simple Google search for &#8220;the best social media plugins for WordPress&#8221; will reveal a plethora of options you can choose from.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How do you pick the one best suited to your needs and goals?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a simple checklist to help you:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Check the Reviews</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first places to start when shopping around for a plugin is to check out user reviews. Good plugins attract a lot of users and positive reviews. Take your time to read a few of the reviews. Doing so will give you an idea of the experience you&#8217;ll expect from the plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if it&#8217;s a new plugin, you can expect it to have few users. This shouldn&#8217;t automatically disqualify it. Instead, you should still check the reviews to better understand the plugin&#8217;s capabilities.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Do the Developers Regularly Maintain the Plugin?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another crucial factor to consider is whether the plugin is well maintained. The best plugins are regularly updated for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Performance</li><li>Security</li><li>Compatibility with the latest version of WordPress</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see how well maintained a plugin is by visiting its WordPress page. Here you&#8217;ll find all the details you need.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-maintenance.png\" alt=\"When looking for the best social media plugin for WordPress, make sure it\'s well maintained. \" class=\"wp-image-75220\" width=\"713\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-maintenance.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-maintenance-300x156.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-maintenance-600x313.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h3>How Easy is it to Set Up?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A good plugin must be easy to set up and configure. It must have an intuitive user interface (UI) and make it easy to use and update. A plugin that&#8217;s complicated to use is just not worth the investment and effort.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Consider the Customization Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Not all websites are built the same. That&#8217;s because different websites serve different purposes. As a result, each website has unique output preferences regarding social media activity. This makes customization an essential factor to consider when choosing a social media plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>How Good is the Customer Support?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Even the best social media plugins for WordPress can run into issues. That&#8217;s why support is an important factor to consider when looking for a plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"628\" height=\"693\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-support.png\" alt=\"When looking for the best social media plugins for WordPress, check out the customer support.\" class=\"wp-image-75223\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-support.png 628w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-support-272x300.png 272w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-support-600x662.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 628px) 100vw, 628px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The best plugins function exceptionally well, and you may not need support for a long time. But when you do, it&#8217;s good to know that customer support will solve your issue quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7 Best Social Media Plugins for WordPress You Should Definitely Check Out</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what to look for as you shop for the best social media plugins for WordPress, let&#8217;s dive in and get you one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/smashballoon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Smash Balloon\">Smash Balloon</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/smashballoon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Smash Balloon\">Smash Balloon</a> is trusted by over 1.6 million websites (including Coca-Cola and Chick-Fil-A, among others). This undoubtedly makes it the best social media plugin for WordPress sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/smashballoon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"285\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-smashballoon.png\" alt=\"Smash Ballon is undoubtedly one of the best social media plugins for WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-75224\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-smashballoon.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-smashballoon-300x122.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-smashballoon-600x244.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The beauty of Smash Balloon is that you can easily display social media content anywhere on your WordPress site. This is all thanks to the Feed Creation Wizard. What&#8217;s more, all feeds are beautifully designed, responsive, and SEO-friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Smash Balloon is actually a combination of several insanely powerful social media plugins. Each is designed to help you seamlessly integrate a social media platform into your WordPress site. The main plugins you can expect from this one of a kind social media toolset include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Custom Facebook Feed Pro</strong>: Allows you to easily display your Facebook photos, albums, events, videos, Facebook Group content, and more.</li><li><strong>Instagram Feed Pro</strong>: This powerful tool enables you to integrate your Instagram account with your website. You can display Instagram hashtag feeds, &#8220;shoppable&#8221; feeds, Instagram Stories, IGTV videos, and much more.</li><li><strong>Custom Twitter Feeds Pro</strong>: Showcase Twitter feeds on your site, including posts that mention your account.</li><li><strong>Feeds for YouTube Pro</strong>: Display YouTube feeds, playlists, live streaming videos, and more.</li><li><strong>Social Wall Pro</strong>: Combine feeds from Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, and YouTube into a powerful social media wall.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most significant advantages that Smash Balloon has over other social media plugins is its ease of use. Even if you&#8217;re not tech-savvy, it&#8217;s super easy to customize your social media feeds any way you want. Smash Balloon allows you to choose from different feed layouts and select which content to show or hide. You also have total control over the displaying follow buttons, likes, comments, shares, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While Smash Balloon has a free version, the paid plans give you more mileage to reach your social media marketing goals. You can get the entire toolset for $299/year. If you want to get each plugin separately, pricing starts at $49/year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"RafflePress\">RafflePress</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking for a social media plugin that makes running contests easier?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Rafflepress\">Rafflepress</a> is the social media plugin for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"680\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-rafflepress.png\" alt=\"RafflePress is one of the best social media plugins for WordPress if you\'re looking to run contests.\" class=\"wp-image-75225\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-rafflepress.png 680w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-rafflepress-300x143.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-rafflepress-600x287.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Social media contests and giveaways are a fantastic way of driving traffic to your website. They&#8217;re also a great way to grow your social media following. Rafflepress will help you do just that. An example of the contests you can run is the popular refer-a-friend giveaway. It&#8217;s a great way to supercharge your growth, both on social media and directly on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of RafflePress&#8217;s best features is its ease of use. Coming with a drag-and-drop giveaway builder and tons of pre-built viral giveaway templates, creating a viral giveaway is as easy as ABC. Also, RafflePress’s templates are designed to help improve social engagement. They&#8217;re also optimized to help increase your traffic and grow your audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wondering which social media platforms RaflePress supports?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RafflePress seamlessly integrates with major social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, and Twitter. No matter which platform you want to integrate to your WordPress site, some notable features of RafflePress include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/google-amp-future-of-mobile-seo/\" title=\"Mobile responsive\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Mobile-responsive</a></li><li>1-click entry and fraud protection&nbsp;</li><li>Tracking and retargeting</li><li>Built-in landing page</li><li>Integrates with email marketing tools and CRMs</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>No matter the type of contest you want to run on social media, RafflePress is the best plugin to help you achieve your goals.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RafflePress does have a free plan. But as can be expected, it&#8217;s limited in functionality. To get the plugin&#8217;s full functionality, you&#8217;ll need to get a paid plan. Those start at $39.50/year for a single site license.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>&nbsp;3. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/social-warfare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Social Warfare\">Social Warfare</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another powerful social media plugin that must be on your radar is <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/social-warfare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Social Warfare\">Social Warfare</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/social-warfare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-social-warfare.png\" alt=\"Social Warfare is a powerful social media plugin that supercharges engagement.\" class=\"wp-image-75226\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-social-warfare.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-social-warfare-300x134.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-social-warfare-600x268.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Social Warfare comes with a beautiful, easy-to-use user interface and packs a lot of features. Some of the features that have made users fall in love with the plugin include:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Powerful analytics dashboard</strong>: Easily track your social shares with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Google Analytics.\">Google Analytics.</a></li><li><strong>Popular posts widget</strong>: Use a widget to display your most popular posts from your blog. Popular posts are automatically calculated according to the number of shares.</li><li><strong>Easy share count recovery</strong>: Even when you switch <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-permalink-structure/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"permalink structures\">permalink structures</a>, you can easily recover your share counts.</li><li><strong>Lightweight</strong>: Unlike other social media plugins, Social Warfare doesn&#8217;t slow down your pages as it only loads necessary scripts.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides these fantastic features, you also get complete control over the content people share on social networks and how they share it. Social Warfare also allows you to add custom images, titles, and descriptions to your posts. This helps boost clicks, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"increase traffic\">increase traffic</a>, and drive engagement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How much will Social Warfare cost you?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Social Warfare is free. However, if you want the paid version (Social Warfare Pro), a single site license will set you back $29/year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/elegant-themes-monarch-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Monarch\">Monarch</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Elegant Themes are known for creating top-selling <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-themes-for-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"WordPress themes\">WordPress themes</a> like Divi. They&#8217;ve also built one of the best social media plugins for WordPress — <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/elegant-themes-monarch-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Monarch\">Monarch</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/elegant-themes-monarch-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-monarch.png\" alt=\"Monarch is another excellent social media plugin for WordPress you should consider.\" class=\"wp-image-75227\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-monarch.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-monarch-300x107.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-monarch-600x214.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>With Monarch, you get to enjoy versatility regarding where you can add share buttons. You have five locations from which to choose from, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Floating sidebar</li><li>Above or below content</li><li>On multimedia like images and videos</li><li>Automatic popups</li><li>Automatic fly-in</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides making it easy for your website visitors to share your content, Monarch is also helpful in converting your website visitors into social media followers. That&#8217;s because, with Monarch, you can easily place social follow buttons in your sidebar. You can also use a shortcode within your page/post content to do the same. Other features you&#8217;ll enjoy with this social media plugin include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Lightning fast&nbsp;</li><li>Highly customizable</li><li>Supports most social media platforms</li><li>Mobile friendly</li><li>Display network names and share counts</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to flexibility, it doesn&#8217;t get better than Monarch. Thankfully, pricing is simple and not complicated as Monarch comes with two plans — $89/year and one-time lifetime access of $249.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/novashare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Novashare\">Novashare</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When looking for the best social media plugin for WordPress, you&#8217;ll undoubtedly want to consider <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/novashare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Novashare\">Novashare</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/novashare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=nofolow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"390\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-novashare.png\" alt=\"Another plugin to consider as you look for the best social media plugin for WordPress is Novashare.\" class=\"wp-image-75228\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-novashare.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-novashare-300x167.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-novashare-600x334.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Novashare lets you add beautiful social sharing buttons to your WordPress website without slowing down your site. This means despite adding more functionality to your website, your pages will still load fast, thereby ensuring your user experience (UX) is unaffected. Notable features of the plugin include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Share buttons and share counters</li><li>Lightweight and fast</li><li>Click to Tweet block</li><li>Share count recovery</li><li>Pinterest hover pins</li><li>Analytics and URL shortening</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll also love that Novashare integrates with most social platforms, including Buffer, WhatsApp, SMS, Telegram, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For such a versatile social media plugin, you&#8217;ll be surprised to know that it&#8217;s quite affordable. A single site license, for example, only costs $24.95/year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/revive-post/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Revive Old Post\">Revive Old Post</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/revive-post/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Revive Old Post\">Revive Old Post</a> is the best social media plugin for WordPress designed to make social media marketing and automation easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/revive-post/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"373\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-revive-social.png\" alt=\"Revive Old Post is a powerful social media plugin that makes it easy to schedule old and new posts.\" class=\"wp-image-75229\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-revive-social.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-revive-social-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-revive-social-600x320.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>One feature that makes Revive Old Post a much-loved social media plugin is the scheduling function. This allows you to automatically set a schedule for how often you want your old and new content to be shared. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this function, you can save on costly social media management tools. Other features that make Revive Old Post one of the best social media plugins for WordPress are:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>RSS to social media sharing</li><li>Auto WordPress post share&nbsp;</li><li>Social media analytics</li><li>Automatic hashtag creation from blog posts</li><li>Granular filters to exclude specific posts out of feeds</li><li>Share old posts</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Revive Old Post is a game-changer if you&#8217;re looking for a social media plugin that enables you to share current and past content on your social profiles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If this sounds like the best social media plugin for you, expect to spend $75/year for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/nextend-social-login/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Nextend Social Login\">Nextend Social Login</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking for a social media plugin that makes it easy for visitors to log in using their social media profiles?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then take a look at <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/nextend-social-login/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Nextend Social Login\">Nextend Social Login</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/nextend-social-login/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"rel=nofollow noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"327\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-nextend-social-login.png\" alt=\"Nextend Social Login is an excellent option if you\'re looking for a plugin that enables users to login with their social media profiles.\" class=\"wp-image-75230\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-nextend-social-login.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-nextend-social-login-300x140.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-nextend-social-login-600x280.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding social login to your eCommerce store or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-membership-plugin-for-wordpress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"WordPress membership site\">WordPress membership site</a> is a great way to boost conversions. One reason for that is it reduces the number of steps needed to create a profile/account.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s what Nextend Social Login was built for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Nextend Social Login, you can allow visitors to your website to register and log in using their social profiles. It supports user login with Facebook, Google, Twitter, LinkedIn and other social networks. The plugin even has support for other popular platforms like Apple, Microsoft, Github, Discord, PayPal, Slack, and many more. Nextend Social Login also allows users to use their social profiles to log in and leave a comment on your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Running a money-making website?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll be happy to know that Nextend Social Login works well with all major WordPress registration and eCommerce plugins. Examples include WooCommerce, Easy Digital Downloads, BuddyPress, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can get started with Nextend Social Login for free. While the free plan will give you a taste of what the plugin can do, it doesn&#8217;t support all the popular platforms. You&#8217;ll have to upgrade to a paid plan. These start at $49/year for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Bonus Social Media Plugin for WordPress: AIOSEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is not a dedicated social media plugin. Instead, it&#8217;s an SEO toolkit with some social media functionality.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"555\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-aioseo-1-1.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO also qualifies to be among the best social media plugins for WordPress as it is packed with powerful social media SEO features.\" class=\"wp-image-75247\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-aioseo-1-1.png 555w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/best-social-media-plugin-for-WordPress-plugin-aioseo-1-1-300x222.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One way AIOSEO functions as a social media plugin is that it helps you display the right images and content when someone shares a page from your site. This is through the proper and reliable use of metadata in your content. Other functionalities that make AIOSEO an excellent social media plugin include that it enables you to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Set custom thumbnails for Facebook</li><li>Set up Twitter cards so you can get rich snippets on Twitter</li><li>Get a full social preview for each post and page from right inside the WordPress block editor</li><li>Enter social media ownership verification codes needed to claim ownership of your page&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These, and more, are the reasons AIOSEO makes for an excellent social media plugin for WordPress sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best Social Media Plugins for WordPress: Time to Pick One</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the best social media plugin for your WordPress is no easy task. With so many options, it can be confusing to know which will best suit your needs.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why we decided to help you by whittling down the selection to the best eight plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, even though this list is short, concluding on your plugin of choice can still be challenging.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To help you pick the best social media plugin for your needs, here are our suggestions:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>For a plugin that helps you display your social media feeds on your site, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/smashballoon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Smash Balloon\">Smash Balloon</a> is your best bet.</li><li>If you&#8217;re looking for a premium solution to supercharge social sharing and engagement, you can&#8217;t go wrong with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/social-warfare/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Social Warfare\">Social Warfare</a>.</li><li>However, if you&#8217;re looking for the best free social media plugin for WordPress, then <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/add-to-any/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"AddToAny Share Buttons\">AddToAny Share Buttons</a> is it.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Whichever social media plugin you choose, remember that social and SEO work hand-in-hand to drive traffic to your site. That&#8217;s why you must also install one of the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"best SEO plugins\">best SEO plugins</a> in the WordPress ecosystem. AIOSEO fits that bill perfectly. What&#8217;s more, it plays nicely with all your other plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, go ahead and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"download AIOSEO today\">download AIOSEO today</a>. It will help you up your social media game. But, more importantly, it will help you drive more organic traffic from search engine results pages to your site.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-social-media-plugins-for-wordpress-compared/\">The 7 Best Social Media Plugins for WordPress (Compared)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://aioseo.com/best-social-media-plugins-for-wordpress-compared/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site (Easy Way)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:164:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 17 Feb 2022 13:30:34 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"google analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=74740\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:455:\"<p>Do you want to know how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site? Google Analytics is a vital tool for every website owner or administrator. It shows how your audience interacts with your website and gives you invaluable&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site (Easy Way)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25819:\"<p>Do you want to know how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Analytics is a vital tool for every website owner or administrator. It shows how your audience interacts with your website and gives you invaluable data to help power your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"SEO efforts\">SEO efforts</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Getting audience insights is important as it helps you optimize your website for engagement and conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why you need to know how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site. We&#8217;ll show you how to do that the easy way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3 Reasons Why Installing Google Analytics on a WordPress Site is Important</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re running or managing a website, one of the most important additions you should make to your toolset is Google Analytics (GA).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why is it so important?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Gives You Insight into Who Visits Your Site</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>GA is an invaluable tool that lets you know who visits your website. It shows you, among many other audience factors, the geographical location of your visitor and the browser used.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Analytics also shows you how people find your website. This is usually via sources like search engines, direct traffic (from emails, for example), referral links from other websites, and more. Knowing where <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"your traffic\">your traffic</a> comes from is crucial to optimizing your acquisition channels.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Shows You Audience Interactions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing what your visitors do when they land on your site is important. Engagement metrics are important to track as they show you:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Posts that drive the most traffic and revenue</li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/posts-vs-pages-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"Posts and pages\">Posts and pages</a> that have the highest bounce rates</li><li>The kind of content users are looking for</li><li>Links that get the most clicks</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>All this data is critical to helping you improve conversion rates, decrease bounce rates, and grow your business more efficiently. It can also help you craft better content and optimized marketing campaigns.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Know Which Pages Drive the Most Revenue</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re running a revenue-generating website, it’s crucial to understand which pages drive the most revenue. You can get this data from GA. You can also see how customers move through the checkout process and engage with your content. This will help you build more efficient buyer journeys.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can do a whole lot more with GA on your website. That’s why you must know how to set it up on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site: Start by Creating a Google Analytics Account</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As promised, we’re going to show you how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site — the easy way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, before we get to that, you must first create a GA account if you don&#8217;t have one already.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Creating a Google Analytics Account</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To create a GA account, you’ll need a Gmail address. You can easily create it if you don&#8217;t have one.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have a Gmail address, you can head to the Google Analytics signup page and create your account. Here’s how:</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Setting Up Your Google Analytics Account</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Using your Gmail credentials, sign in to Google Analytics and follow the prompts to set up your account. One of the first steps in this stage is to fill in your information, including the account name. The account name will be used internally, so you can use any name that makes sense to you, like your business/website name.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"269\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-account-details.png\" alt=\"The first step in knowing how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site is to create a Google Analytics account.\" class=\"wp-image-74831\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-account-details.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-account-details-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-account-details-600x231.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll also be asked to name your property (website) and fill in other information about your business. The business information includes what you want to track with GA.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"743\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-business-info.png\" alt=\"Setting up your Google Analytics account involves submitting your business information. \" class=\"wp-image-74832\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-business-info.png 512w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-business-info-207x300.png 207w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve ticked all the appropriate boxes, you can then click “Create.” Doing so will take you to a page where you’ll be requested to agree to the Google Analytics terms of service.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"593\" height=\"509\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-terms-of-service.png\" alt=\"To continue with the setup, you\'ll have to agree to Google\'s terms of service agreement.\" class=\"wp-image-74833\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-terms-of-service.png 593w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-terms-of-service-300x258.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 593px) 100vw, 593px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After this, a window will open and you’ll be required to select your email newsletter preferences. Next, you’ll be taken to your Google Analytics admin dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"292\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-web.png\" alt=\"When asked to select a data stream to track, select &quot;web.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-74834\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-web.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-web-300x125.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-web-600x250.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Determine The Type of Web Asset You Want to Track</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first steps to take once on the admin dashboard is to select the kind of web asset you’ll be tracking. In this case, you’ll choose “Web”. Once you do that, you’ll be prompted to set up a data stream:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"362\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-data-stream.png\" alt=\"When learning how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site, you\'ll be asked to set up a data stream.\" class=\"wp-image-74836\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-data-stream.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-data-stream-300x155.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-data-stream-600x310.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, the setup wizard will present you with your web stream details and the Google Analytics tracking code to paste on your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No coding skills?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t worry. As promised, we’ll show you how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site — the easy way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site (Easy Way): Using MonsterInsights</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Using a plugin is the easiest way to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site. In this regard, no plugin beats <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"MonsterInsights\">MonsterInsights</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember the tracking code you got in the last stage of setting up GA?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Typically, you would have to inject that into your website’s code. However, with MonsterInsights, you don’t have to fiddle with any code. This makes MonsterInsights an excellent tool for both experts and novices alike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started with MonsterInsights, you must first download and activate the plugin. Doing so requires you to log into your MonsterInsights account and download the plugin zip file. Once you’ve done that, go to your WordPress Dashboard, navigate to the “Upload Plugin” option, and select “Upload”.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"644\" height=\"199\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-1.png\" alt=\"To use the MonsterInsights way, yuou must first upload the plugin.\" class=\"wp-image-74837\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-1.png 644w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-1-300x93.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-1-600x185.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 644px) 100vw, 644px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll then be prompted to select the file you want to upload.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"683\" height=\"248\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-2.png\" alt=\"To upload MonsterInsights, log in to your MonsterInsights account, download the zip file, and upload it in the add plugin section of WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-74838\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-2.png 683w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-2-300x109.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-2-600x218.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the zip file you just downloaded, then click “Install Now.” Doing so will upload the file and install MonsterInsights on your site. Once the plugin has been uploaded, click the “Activate” button to activate the plugin. The setup wizard will guide you on how to complete the process.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Setting Up MonsterInsights</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to setting up MonsterInsights is to select the type of website you’re connecting to. You have three options — Business website, Publisher (Blog), and eCommerce. Select the most applicable option, then click “Save and Continue.” Next, you&#8217;ll be taken to a page where you’ll be asked to enter your license key.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"599\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-verify.png\" alt=\"Setting up MonsterInsights involves verifying your account by entering a license key.\" class=\"wp-image-74841\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-verify.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-verify-300x257.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-verify-600x513.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once the license key is verified, click the “Connect MonsterInsights” button.&nbsp; You’ll then be prompted to choose the Google Account you used to create your GA account. Doing so will take you to a page where you’ll grant MonsterInsights the proper permissions to access your analytics data.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"449\" height=\"863\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-permissions.png\" alt=\"To connect MonsterInsights to your Google Analytics account, you\'ll have to give MonsterInsights permission to access your GA data.\" class=\"wp-image-74844\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-permissions.png 449w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-permissions-156x300.png 156w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 449px) 100vw, 449px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Click “Allow,” and the setup wizard will take you to a page where you’re to select the profile you want to connect to GA. If you have many web properties, make sure to pick the right one.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-select-blog.png\" alt=\"Select your blog and click &quot;Complete Connection.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-74846\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-select-blog.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-select-blog-300x184.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-select-blog-600x369.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;Click “Complete Connection.” The plugin will perform a final authentication. Once this is complete, you’ll be taken back to the MonsterInsights setup page. Here, you’ll be presented with recommended settings (enabled by default), which include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Events Tracking</li><li>Enhanced Link Attribution&nbsp;</li><li>File Download Tracking</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll also find more advanced settings that you have to enable if they apply to your website type and goals. At the very bottom, you have the option to allow auto-updates of the plugin. We recommend you set this to on, making it easier for you to keep the plugin updated.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Review and configure your settings, then click “Save and Continue.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next page will show you addons you can install to make MonsterInsights more versatile in the data it tracks.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"620\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-recommendations.png\" alt=\"Select the addons that will help you get the best out of MonsterInsights data tracking and reporting.\" class=\"wp-image-74850\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-recommendations.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-recommendations-300x233.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-recommendations-600x466.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Install the addons you need and click “Save and Continue,” and you&#8217;ll be taken to the final step of the setup.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"751\" height=\"701\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-finish.png\" alt=\"On the last page of the setup, click &quot;Finish Setup and Exit Wizard.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-74845\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-finish.png 751w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-finish-300x280.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-finish-600x560.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Click “Finish Setup and Exit Wizard,” and you’re all done. You’ve just set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site. You can now see your website’s performance metrics right from your WordPress dashboard. To do that, click on the “Insights” option in your WordPress dashboard and select “Reports.”</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"269\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-report.png\" alt=\"When you know how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site, you can access reports right from within your dashboard.\" class=\"wp-image-74853\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-report.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-report-300x115.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-monster-insights-report-600x231.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can view different reports by clicking on the tabs at the top of the report page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While you can get tons of valuable insights using MonsterInsights Lite, you&#8217;ll need the Pro version to unlock advanced features. These include tracking your e-commerce store&#8217;s performance, insights into where your traffic comes from, your top landing pages, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site Using the Insert Header and Footers Plugin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Another easy way of setting up GA on your WordPress site is by using the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Insert Header and Footers\">Insert Header and Footers</a> plugin by <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"WPBeginner\">WPBeginner</a>. The plugin enables you to inject code into your WordPress website without doing the coding yourself. The only caveat is that, unlike the MonsterInsights way, you won’t be able to view your analytics data in your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll first have to install and activate the Insert Header and Footers plugin to use this method. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, head over to your GA account and copy your tracking code. You’ll find this by going to the “Admin” section then selecting the “Data Streams” option. Doing so will open a page displaying your web properties.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"234\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-data-streams.png\" alt=\"Select the web property whose code you want to copy.\" class=\"wp-image-74835\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-data-streams.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-data-streams-300x100.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-data-streams-600x201.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting the web property whose code snippet you need will open up its streaming details. Then, on the “web stream details” page, click on the “global site tag” option under the “Tagging Instructions” section. Doing so will expand the section to show your GA code snippet.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"340\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-code-2.png\" alt=\"When learning how to set up Google Analytics on a WordPress site, you\'ll have to copy the tracking code from your GA admin dashboard.\" class=\"wp-image-74854\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-code-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-code-2-300x146.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-analytics-code-2-600x291.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the code you’ll have to paste in your website’s header to enable GA to track analytics on your website. Copy this code and head over to your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once in WordPress, select the “Settings” option and click on “Header and Footer.”</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"257\" height=\"502\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footers.png\" alt=\"Once in WordPress, select the “Settings” option and click on “Header and Footer.”\" class=\"wp-image-74855\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footers.png 257w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footers-154x300.png 154w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 257px) 100vw, 257px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This will lead to a window that gives you many options to paste your code.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"415\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footer-script.png\" alt=\"Paste your code in the Head Page Section Injection space and click “Save.”\" class=\"wp-image-74856\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footer-script.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footer-script-300x178.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site-header-and-footer-script-600x356.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paste your code in the &lt;Head&gt; Page Section Injection space and click “Save.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s it! You’ve set up Google Analytics on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Google Analytics: An Invaluable Resource for Every Web Admin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Understanding what’s happening on your WordPress website is critical to improving your engagement and conversions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why setting up Google Analytics is essential.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Targeted tracking will help you understand your audience better, thereby enabling you to create content tailored to their needs. The wealth of data that GA provides is helpful for monitoring SEO performance. It’s also valuable for helping you improve your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-best-practices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"SEO strategy\">SEO strategy</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why setting up GA on your site must be a priority. It’s as important as installing an SEO plugin like AIOSEO. AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market. It automates the SEO tasks you need to perform on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you set up Google Analytics on your WordPress website, make sure to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"download AIOSEO\">download AIOSEO</a> too.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site (Easy Way)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:154:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 14 Feb 2022 14:09:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"ading Google AdSense to WordPress site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Google AdSense\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"how to add Google AdSense to a WordPress site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=73754\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:416:\"<p>Want to know how to add Google AdSense to a WordPress site? If you plan on monetizing your website, one of the many avenues you can take is to run ads on your site. That&#8217;s where Google AdSense comes in.&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22856:\"<p>Want to know how to add Google AdSense to a WordPress site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you plan on monetizing your website, one of the many avenues you can take is to run ads on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s where Google AdSense comes in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is Google AdSense (and Why Should You Consider It)?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Google AdSense is an online advertising network that enables publishers, content creators, and website owners to monetize their websites by displaying relevant ads to their visitors. Because the ads are highly targeted, they&#8217;re usually effective and bring the advertisers a good return on ad spend (ROAS). As a result, the demand for ad space is always high.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google AdSense is the best way to go for publishers who want to cash in on the high demand for ad space. One reason is that it&#8217;s the largest advertising network and therefore offers more opportunities to both publishers and advertisers. Another reason you should consider Google AdSense is that it&#8217;s hassle-free. You don&#8217;t have to deal directly with advertisers. Instead, Google handles all publisher/advertiser relationships, including collecting payments on your behalf.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Setting Up Your AdSense Account</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to add Google AdSense to your WordPress site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to adding Google AdSense to your website is to <a href=\"https://www.google.com/adsense/start/\" title=\"sign up for an AdSense account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">sign up for an AdSense account</a>. If you already have a Gmail account, you can use that account to sign up. You&#8217;ll then be asked to fill out a super short form.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Google AdSense team will then review your application, a process that may take anything from a few hours to weeks. However, you can still get a snippet of code you can paste on your site to verify and connect it to AdSense.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get the code, click on the &#8220;Get code&#8221; button and a page with a snippet of code will open:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-2.png\" alt=\"When learning how to Add Google Adsense to a WordPress site you\'ll need to copy a snippet of code from AdSense to your website.\" class=\"wp-image-73757\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-2-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-2-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll have to place the code on your website to start displaying ads. We&#8217;ll see how to do that in a&nbsp; moment.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What Happens if Your Account Isn&#8217;t Approved?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, your application for a Google AdSense account can get rejected. When this happens, Google will send you an email explaining why your account application was disapproved. In many cases, the rejection may be due to issues regarding your website. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Lack of content/poor quality content</li><li>Security issues</li><li>Plagiarized content</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Google is in the business of selling ad space to the highest bidder. Because of this, they want to know that the ads are being placed on high-quality websites that attract quality traffic. This is why they&#8217;re strict about website quality.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What do you do when your application is disapproved?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of immediately reapplying, consider auditing your site first. Find any issues that may be the cause and fix them. Work on any security issues you find and publish content that meets Google&#8217;s quality rater guidelines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re satisfied that you&#8217;ve solved the problems Google highlighted, you can reapply for an AdSense account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, whatever the case, you don&#8217;t have to wait until your account is approved to connect your website to Google AdSense.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s get to it then, shall we?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Manually Place the Google AdSense Verification Code in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides using a plugin to connect your Google AdSense to WordPress, you can also do it manually. This will require you to edit your theme code — nothing heavy, though.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember the code you got as you were setting up your AdSense account?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where you&#8217;ll need it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To connect your Adsense to your WordPress site, you&#8217;ll first have to click on the &#8220;Appearance&#8221; tab in your WordPress dashboard and select &#8220;Theme Editor.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"348\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor.png\" alt=\"knowing how to add Google AdSense to a WordPress site involves editing your theme\'s header.php file. \" class=\"wp-image-73760\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve opened the theme editor, select the header.php file under the &#8220;Theme Files&#8221; section. Place your AdSense code just above the &lt;/head&gt; tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-header-php.png\" alt=\"Add the code just above the header tag in your header.php file.\" class=\"wp-image-73762\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-header-php.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-header-php-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-theme-editor-header-php-600x293.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done, click &#8220;Update File,&#8221; and that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Editing your theme&#8217;s code is not recommended, especially if you&#8217;re not familiar with editing theme files and code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#8217;s the recommended route?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use a plugin to place your Adsense verification code in your header and footer.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Using a Plugin to Place the Google AdSense Verification Code in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Plugins make life easy for website admins. Fortunately, there&#8217;s a plugin for every function you may want to perform on your WordPress website. That includes connecting your AdSense to</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site Using the Insert Header and Footers Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the easiest ways to connect Google Adsense to your WordPress site is to use a plugin like <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Insert Header and Footers\">Insert Header and Footers</a> by WPBeginner.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve installed and activated the Insert Header and Footers plugin, go to the &#8220;Settings&#8221; tab in your WordPress dashboard. Then, click &#8220;Insert Header and Footers&#8221;:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"460\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers.png\" alt=\"You\'ll find Insert Header and Footers under the settings section of your WordPress dashboard. \" class=\"wp-image-73764\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers.png 460w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers-300x277.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 460px) 100vw, 460px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>When you open the &#8220;Insert Headers and Footers&#8221; link, you&#8217;ll be led to a page with three empty spaces where you can enter code snippets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers-1.png\" alt=\"Paste your AdSense code in the “Scripts in Header” box.\" class=\"wp-image-73765\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers-1-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-insert-headers-footers-1-600x279.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Paste your Google AdSense verification code in the &#8220;Scripts in Header&#8221; box and click &#8220;Save.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like that, you&#8217;ve added the Google AdSense verification code to your WordPress site. Your site is now connected to Google AdSense.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site Using the Advanced Ads Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the easiest ways to connect Google AdSense to your WordPress site is to use a plugin. While there are many you can use for this, we highly recommend <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/advanced-ads/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"Advanced Ads\">Advanced Ads</a>. It&#8217;s easy to use and offers more flexibility than most plugins in the same category.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest advantage of using a plugin is that you don&#8217;t have to mess with the code on your website. Another advantage is that a plugin can manage the process of managing the process of displaying ads without you using widgets. Advanced Ads also gives you a Gutenberg block for ads. This makes it easier to place ads wherever you want to in your posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How do you connect your WordPress site to Google AdSense using a plugin?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, you must install and activate the Advanced Ads plugin. Once installed, head over to the plugin settings and click on the AdSense tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"266\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-1.png\" alt=\"The Advanvced Ads plugin is another easy way to connect Google AdSense to a WordPress site. \" class=\"wp-image-73766\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-1-300x114.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-1-600x228.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the &#8220;Connect to AdSense&#8221; button, and you&#8217;ll be prompted to sign in with the same credentials you used to create your AdSense account. You&#8217;ll also be asked to confirm if you agree to grant the plugin access to your AdSense data. Once that&#8217;s done, your AdSense account information will be displayed on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"434\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-2.png\" alt=\"Your Google AdSense information will be displayed in the plugin\'s dashboard after you connect to AdSense.\" class=\"wp-image-73767\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-2-300x186.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-advanced-ads-2-600x372.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Important note</strong>: tick the &#8220;Auto ads&#8221; checkbox to allow Advanced Ads to insert the AdSense header code in your website&#8217;s header. Doing so will enable you to verify your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll also be asked to enable other settings by ticking relevant checkboxes. Once you do that, save your settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s it! You&#8217;ve connected your Google AdSense account to your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whichever way you insert the code, you&#8217;ll have to verify with Google that the code has been properly placed. To do this, head over to your Adsense account and tick the checkbox to confirm that you&#8217;ve placed the snippet of code on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Creating Google AdSense Units</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An AdSense unit is a placeholder for the ads you&#8217;ll display on your website. You can create many ad units for a single web page, with each ad unit serving a specific type of ad. To create an AdSense ad unit, log in to your AdSense account and click on the &#8220;By ad unit&#8221;:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"324\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit.png\" alt=\"Once you know how to add Google Adsense to a WordPress site, you can now start creating ad units.\" class=\"wp-image-73770\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-600x278.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, select the type of ads you want to display on your site. You have three options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Display ads</li><li>In-feed ads</li><li>In-article ads</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re not sure which ad type to use, we recommend starting with display ads.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking on your ad type, you&#8217;ll be asked to name your ad unit. This is just for internal purposes, specifically to help you manage many different ad units.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"333\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-name-size.png\" alt=\"After clicking on your ad type, you’ll be asked to name your ad unit.\" class=\"wp-image-73771\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-name-size.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-name-size-300x143.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-name-size-600x285.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides naming your ad unit, you&#8217;ll also have to choose your ad size. Responsive ads are the most recommended as they display well across different devices and screen sizes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click the &#8220;Create&#8221; button to continue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AdSense will generate a unique ad code for you when you do this. This contains the ad unit ID and your publisher ID.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-code.png\" alt=\"When you create an ad unit, AdSense will generate a unique ad code for you.\" class=\"wp-image-73772\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-code.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-code-300x183.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-ad-unit-code-600x366.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll use this code to place your ad units on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Placing AdSense Ads on Your WordPress Site&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have your AdSense ad code, you need to determine where to place the ad. In most cases, the sidebar would be your best bet. To place your ad, you&#8217;ll need to use <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/widgets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"WordPress\'s widgets\">WordPress&#8217;s widgets</a>. You&#8217;ll find this under your WordPress dashboard&#8217;s &#8220;Appearance&#8221; section.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"550\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-widgets-1.png\" alt=\"You can place your ads in appropriate places by using widgets.\" class=\"wp-image-73776\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-widgets-1.png 550w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-widgets-1-300x189.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you open the widgets tab, drag and drop the &#8220;Custom HTML&#8221; widget to the widget area you want to place your ad unit. Next, paste your Google AdSense code in there. However, for better ad placement control and tracking, we recommend you use a plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/adsanity/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" title=\"AdSanity\">AdSanity</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Adding Auto-Ads AdSense Code in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Manually placing individual ads on different places of your site is a very time-consuming process. For a beginner, it can be a very challenging task.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google introduced auto-ads to solve this very problem. The auto-ads feature allows you to add one snippet of code to your site and let Google AdSense determine the best location, ad size, and ad type for your site. The only caveat of this method is you have less control over the process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To leverage the auto-ads feature, sign in to your Google AdSense account and click on the &#8220;Ads&#8221; tab. Next, click on &#8220;Get Code&#8221; to generate a code for your auto-ads.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"700\" height=\"288\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code.png\" alt=\"To place auto-ads, you need to generate a codecode from the Ads section of your AdSense account.  \" class=\"wp-image-73777\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-300x123.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site-get-code-600x247.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>As before, copy the code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The auto-ads function uses the same snippet of code to generate ads everywhere on your WordPress site. You need to add the auto-ads code to every page you want ads to be displayed for this to work.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way you can do that is to paste the code into your theme&#8217;s header.php file. However, this is not the best solution, as the code will be erased every time you update your theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best way to add the auto-ads code to your website is by using the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" title=\"Insert Header and Footers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Insert Header and Footers</a> plugin as before.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once inserted, the plugin will add the code to every page on your website. Google AdSense will then automatically display ads on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Now You Know How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site: Go Ahead and Make Some Ad Money!&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve connected Google AdSense to your WordPress site, the money will come rolling in, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, not quite.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ads will only make you money if you drive relevant traffic to them. The two best ways to do that are creating high-quality content and leveraging <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-checklist/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"SEO best practices\">SEO best practices</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can help you with both.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While we don&#8217;t create content, our plugin can help ensure that your content follows readability and SEO best practices. However, our forte lies in SEO. With the AISEO plugin, you can optimize your content and website for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is an easy-to-use, no-code SEO toolkit used by over 3 million users. You can use it for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/top-tips-for-good-on-page-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"on-page SEO\">on-page SEO</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-technical-seo-the-best-checklist-in-2022/\" title=\"technical SEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">technical SEO</a>, thereby increasing the chances of your content and ads being seen by the right people.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why, if you haven&#8217;t, you should <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"download AIOSEO today\">download AIOSEO today</a>. It&#8217;s an essential tool for every online marketer.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site/\">How to Add Google AdSense to a WordPress Site</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-a-wordpress-site/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base